      {
        "id": "6aa72cbf83f14cbf751f97ddc5a5a477d967c6f9",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2025,
          "name": "Arthur Martella",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "arthur.martella.1@att.com",
          "username": "amartell"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-29 19:24:05.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nNotes about what is included in this patch (pre-merge), as detailed by Enrique:\n\n0. Fix commit to music operation\n  There were some bugs in the original implementation related to the order of operations.\n1. Fix the management of table letter case\n  Save the schema that contains the table.\n2. Implementation of Postgres \n  This is the least important, but it is also the easiest to merge.\n3. Asynchronous retrieval of shadow table\n  This is also low priority, it is meant to speed up the commit.\n4. Selection of Mixin using the properties file\n5. Correctly register drivers and dynamic mixin instances\n6. Fix tests\n7. Fix initializations\n  This is because in the original design, metric nodes initializes tables, this can cause the system to have failures related to schema mismatches, so the cluster configuration should be run, before we start any node in the system.\n8. Fix eventual table configuration\n  In the first design, the eventual tables were treated as a string instead of an array, so to make the configuration json be more intutive I changed the way the structure is treated, as well as other small changes on the configuration json.\n9. Add compression to the tx digest\n10. Parallelize the txdigest and append to redolog operation\n11. Fix Eventual Transactions Operations\n  There were some problems with the order in which they were checked, and also how the eventual data structures were not correctly initialized.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
